Merge pull request #20 from vdloo/endpoint-is-without-kv

endpoint is without /kv

endpoint is without /kv

the default endpoint is now
```
DEFAULT_ENDPOINT = 'http://localhost:8500/v1/'
```

instead of
```
DEFAULT_KV_ENDPOINT = 'http://localhost:8500/v1/kv/'
```

This makes it more sensible to use conn.get_meta. otherwise you'd have
to manually specify the kv-less default endpoint and pass 'kv/' to all
kv items you'd want to interact with.

Merge pull request #19 from vdloo/fix-missing-trailing-slash-regression

fix missing trailing slash regression

fix missing trailing slash regression looks like this trailing slash got lost in the CAS implementation. after the cas implementation: ``` root@T1:/usr/etc/raptiformica_map# curl http://localhost:8500/v1/kv?/recurse=true Moved Permanently. ``` before the cas implementation ``` root@T1:/usr/etc/raptiformica_map# curl http://localhost:8500/v1/kv/?recurse=true [{"LockIndex":0,"Key":"bla/bla","Flags":0,"Value":"blabla==" ``` the old behavior is now restored. I'm not sure if the cas query param also requires that trailing comma though, I've assumed it does.
